---
description: Project-wide engineering rules for Belong
alwaysApply: true
---

You are building Belong, a Next.js App Router app for recurring real-life communities.

Core thesis:
- Belong is not an event discovery app.
- Belong is not a generic community platform.
- Belong is infrastructure for the second visit.
- It helps hosts turn recurring gatherings into warm, retained communities.
- It helps first-timers feel safe showing up alone.

Engineering rules:
- Use TypeScript strictly.
- Prefer small files, small functions, and clear names.
- Do not create duplicate components if an existing component can be reused.
- Do not add new dependencies without explaining why.
- Do not modify unrelated files.
- Before coding, list the files you plan to create or edit.
- After coding, summarize what changed and how to test.
- Never store secrets in code.
- Keep database access server-side only.
- Validate all user input with Zod.
- Prefer boring, reliable architecture over clever abstractions.
- Build thin vertical slices, not broad unfinished features.
- Do not enable React Compiler until the core demo loop works.
